ain't even had breakfast.

6
00:02:49,836 --> 00:02:51,338
Give me the chalk.

7
00:02:56,760 --> 00:03:00,347
Why don't you comb your hair, Sonny?
It sticks up.

8
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:12,984
I'm surprised
you had the nerve to show up...

9
00:03:13,235 --> 00:03:15,487
...after that stomping
you took last night.

10
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,114
What'd you say?

11
00:03:19,491 --> 00:03:20,534
Could've been worse.

12
00:03:21,243 --> 00:03:22,494
Yeah.

13
00:03:23,245 --> 00:03:25,455
You can say that about everything.

14
00:03:29,376 --> 00:03:32,003
A few teams have had
some luck with tackling.

15
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:34,839
Keeps the other team
from scoring so often.

16
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:36,841
Sounds too rough for me.

17
00:03:44,683 --> 00:03:46,977
You don't care
if it was your last game.

18
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:50,730
You'll never get stomped
for your high school ball team again.

19
00:03:50,939 --> 00:03:53,817
- Where's your school spirit?
- Don't know.

20
00:03:57,737 --> 00:03:58,863
You working today?

21
00:03:59,072 --> 00:04:00,907
The truck's being greased.

22
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:29,060
See, this is what I get for betting
on my own hometown ball team.

23
00:04:30,228 --> 00:04:32,147
I ought to have better sense.

24
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:34,816
Wouldn't hurt if you had
a better hometown.

25
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:38,486
Mind pointing that
at the floor till I get by?

26
00:04:38,695 --> 00:04:40,822
I don't want my eye poked out.

27
00:04:43,992 --> 00:04:46,411
Don't let Billy get too far away.

28
00:04:48,663 --> 00:04:53,251
You're damn more dangerous in
a pool hall than on a football field.

29
00:04:57,547 --> 00:04:59,591
You ever heard of tackling?

30
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:18,276
Hey, Duane!

31
00:05:18,485 --> 00:05:20,820
Boy, I froze my ass last night!

32
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:24,365
Why can't you kids learn to tackle?

33
00:05:35,251 --> 00:05:39,297
How about taking Genevieve some
change, as you're going that way?

34
00:05:50,517 --> 00:05:51,976
Toss me one!

35
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:58,733
Look, Larry, they can catch.

36
00:05:58,942 --> 00:06:01,778
Feisty sons of bitches.
Wish they could tackle.

37
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:03,988
Or do something useful.

38
00:06:04,364 --> 00:06:07,575
Team wasn't worth
a kiss-my-ass this year.

39
00:06:16,543 --> 00:06:18,753
Fade out, Crawford. One more time.

40
00:06:22,674 --> 00:06:24,968
All right, you boys. Cut it out.

41
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:28,012
I got enough problems
without you playing that game.

42
00:06:28,221 --> 00:06:31,224
We could've run off to Mexico
with this, you know.

43
00:06:33,977 --> 00:06:36,312
- Play the new one we heard.
- Which one?

44
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:39,774
Down payment on breakfast.
Let someone rich play the jukebox.

45
00:06:39,983 --> 00:06:42,277
Nobody rich would eat here.

46
00:06:48,866 --> 00:06:51,202
- I ain't very hungry.
- Well, I am.

47
00:06:51,452 --> 00:06:53,037
You want the pickup first?

48
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:55,790
I oughtn't always get it first.
It's half yours.

49
00:06:55,999 --> 00:06:57,375
- Go ahead.
- You sure?

50
00:06:57,583 --> 00:07:00,378
Yes. Anyways, I got
lots of deliveries to make.

51
00:07:00,628 --> 00:07:02,714
And I have to go clear to Ranger.

52
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:05,883
I'll be lucky to get back
for the second show.

53
00:07:50,553 --> 00:07:54,974
My goodness, Sonny. Frank oughtn't
work you so late on weekends.

54
00:07:55,224 --> 00:07:56,517
That's what I tell him.

55
00:07:56,768 --> 00:08:00,104
You ain't got in in time
to see the comedy in three weeks.

56
00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:03,149
Hope you don't want popcorn.
There ain't none.

57
00:08:03,524 --> 00:08:05,485
And you missed the newsreel too.

58
00:08:05,735 --> 00:08:09,447
The main show's done started,
so I'll just charge you 30 cents.

59
00:08:09,655 --> 00:08:10,698
Thanks, Miss Mosey.

60
00:08:10,907 --> 00:08:14,952
<i>I was wondering if my daughter had</i>
<i>deserted us, when I heard her voice.</i>

61
00:08:18,748 --> 00:08:20,374
<i>Kay was our only daughter.</i>

62
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:24,670
<i>A father's not supposed to have</i>
<i>favourites, but when it's Kay...</i>

63
00:08:24,921 --> 00:08:27,507
<i>- You smell good.</i>
<i>- You like it?</i>

64
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,718
<i>- What's that?</i>
<i>- An atomizer.</i>

65
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:32,637
<i>What'd you get? A present?</i>

66
00:08:32,845 --> 00:08:33,888
<i>Who from?</i>

67
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:36,098
<i>Somebody.</i>

68
00:08:42,146 --> 00:08:44,732
I decided you had a wreck.

69
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:51,823
<i>What's happened? You look different.</i>

70
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:54,075
<i>- I do?</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

71
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:57,119
<i>You look all lit up inside.</i>

72
00:08:58,621 --> 00:09:01,040
<i>You're not wearing</i>
<i>your usual deadpan look.</i>

73
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:03,751
<i>That "How'd I get</i>
<i>into this family?" look.</i>

74
00:09:04,001 --> 00:09:05,127
<i>Father.</i>

75
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:08,130
<i>You've been taking the vitamins</i>
<i>Dr. Gray sent you.</i>

76
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:09,715
<i>That's right.</i>

77
00:09:23,604 --> 00:09:26,524
<i>I guess I'll get me</i>
<i>some of those vitamins.</i>

78
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:28,568
<i>I'll get it, Delilah.</i>

79
00:09:31,195 --> 00:09:33,489
<i>What's wrong?</i>
<i>She looks kind of queer.</i>

80
00:09:34,282 --> 00:09:35,741
Guess what?

81
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:37,243
What?

82
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:40,204
It's our anniversary.

83
00:09:41,205 --> 00:09:42,456
What?

84
00:09:42,665 --> 00:09:45,960
We've been going steady
a year tonight.

85
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:47,670
Yeah?

86
00:09:49,463 --> 00:09:51,465
Seems like a lot longer.

87
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:55,428
You should've got me
some anniversary present.

88
00:09:55,636 --> 00:09:58,556
You can have another stick of gum.
That's all I got.

89
00:09:58,764 --> 00:10:02,977
You can give me the dollar
it cost me and Marlene for the show.

90
00:10:03,227 --> 00:10:06,063
What are y'all doing
back here in the dark?

91
00:10:08,482 --> 00:10:09,900
<i>He's coming for me soon.</i>

92
00:10:10,109 --> 00:10:11,736
<i>I'll get your coffee.</i>

93
00:10:14,613 --> 00:10:15,823
<i>Where'd the boys go?</i>

94
00:10:16,032 --> 00:10:19,201
<i>Ben had some date.</i>
<i>Tommy's at basketball practice.</i>

95
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:21,787
<i>- Bring the coffee, please.</i>
<i>- Yes, Miss Banks.</i>

96
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:26,083
I don't see why they should get
the pickup first all the time.

97
00:10:26,792 --> 00:10:29,545
All they ever want to do
is neck anyway.

98
00:10:31,047 --> 00:10:33,966
<i>Buckley says it's not too young</i>
<i>for a man to marry.</i>

99
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:36,677
<i>I didn't marry your mother</i>
<i>till I was 25.</i>

100
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:45,603
- Need some help, Jessie?
- Yeah, sure do.

101
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:47,938
- So long, Sam.
- Bye.

102
00:10:48,981 --> 00:10:52,276
- Sure did like the picture.
- Well, good.

103
00:11:34,276 --> 00:11:36,570
Crack your window.
Leave the motor on.

104
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:38,489
It's just too cold in here.

105
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:53,546
Your hands are like ice.

106
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:55,881
Put on my gloves.

107
00:12:15,192 --> 00:12:18,445
What's the matter with you?
You act plain bored.

108
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:21,156
Quit.

109
00:12:21,365 --> 00:12:22,408
Quit.

110
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:25,077
You said this was our anniversary.

111
00:12:25,286 --> 00:12:27,329
Let's do something different.

112
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:30,624
Well, I like that. You cheapskate.

113
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:34,420
Didn't get me a present,
and now you want to get me pregnant.

114
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:37,006
My God, Charlene!
It was just my hand.

115
00:12:37,214 --> 00:12:38,924
One thing leads to another.

116
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:41,719
My mama told me
how that old stuff goes.

117
00:12:42,011 --> 00:12:45,180
We'll have plenty of time for that
when we get married.

118
00:12:45,889 --> 00:12:47,683
You wasn't no livelier than me.

119
00:12:47,891 --> 00:12:51,979
Because you ain't good-looking enough.
You ain't even got a ducktail.

120
00:12:52,187 --> 00:12:54,273
Well, anyway, I'm done late.

121
00:12:54,523 --> 00:12:56,275
Let's go on home.

122
00:12:56,525 --> 00:12:58,736
Some anniversary.

123
00:12:59,945 --> 00:13:03,699
If that's the way you feel about it,
I'd just as soon break up.

124
00:13:03,907 --> 00:13:06,869
I don't want to spoil
no more anniversaries for you.

125
00:13:07,077 --> 00:13:09,371
That's the way
nice girls get treated.

126
00:13:09,580 --> 00:13:11,665
I might've known
you wasn't dependable.

127
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:13,792
You wasn't even in the backfield.

128
00:13:14,001 --> 00:13:17,463
This jacket's got a hole,
but don't ask me to sew it for you.

129
00:13:17,713 --> 00:13:19,548
Give me back my pictures too.

130
00:13:19,798 --> 00:13:23,052
I don't want you showing them
and telling how hot I am.

131
00:13:23,260 --> 00:13:25,220
You wasn't very hot.

132
00:13:50,537 --> 00:13:52,998
I hope you ain't down about Charlene.

133
00:13:53,207 --> 00:13:57,044
- I ain't blue about her.
- What are you blue about then?

134
00:13:57,419 --> 00:13:59,588
Ain't nobody to go with in this town.

135
00:13:59,797 --> 00:14:03,175
Jacy's the only pretty girl in school,
and Duane's got her.

136
00:14:03,384 --> 00:14:05,511
I'd call that his tough luck.

137
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:08,972
You don't have to eat so fast.
You ain't in a race.

138
00:14:09,348 --> 00:14:12,684
Jacy'd bring you more misery
than she'll ever be worth.

139
00:14:15,687 --> 00:14:17,356
Did your dad give you this?

140
00:14:17,815 --> 00:14:19,691
He needs all he's got.

141
00:14:19,942 --> 00:14:24,071
Wouldn't hurt you to take something
from him once in a while.

142
00:14:24,279 --> 00:14:27,533
I don't know. You and Duane
both in a boarding house.

143
00:14:27,991 --> 00:14:31,453
Him with the mother and you
with the father. Don't seem right.

144
00:14:32,538 --> 00:14:35,666
And your dad's taking
too many pills, you know.

145
00:14:37,835 --> 00:14:39,128
But I'm no one to talk.

146
00:14:39,336 --> 00:14:41,588
I never got on with Mama.
I still don't.

147
00:14:41,797 --> 00:14:44,258
I hear Dan's going back to work soon.

148
00:14:44,466 --> 00:14:46,718
I guess you'll be quitting
before long.

149
00:14:48,053 --> 00:14:51,974
We got $4000 worth
of doctor bills to pay.

150
00:14:52,891 --> 00:14:56,854
I will probably be making
cheeseburgers for your grandkids.

151
00:15:38,228 --> 00:15:43,108
What are my chances this morning
of interesting you kids in John Keats?

152
00:15:43,358 --> 00:15:44,610
None at all.

153
00:15:48,906 --> 00:15:50,365
Joe Bob?

154
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:53,327
I read that poem of his
about the nightingale.

155
00:15:53,535 --> 00:15:55,329
I didn't think it was so good.

156
00:15:55,537 --> 00:15:58,206
Sounded like he wanted
to be a nightingale.

157
00:15:58,498 --> 00:16:02,377
I don't think he wanted
to be a nightingale, Joe Bob.

158
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:04,755
Maybe he just wanted to be immortal.

159
00:16:05,005 --> 00:16:08,759
All you have to do to be immortal
is lead a good Christian life.

160
00:16:08,967 --> 00:16:11,428
Anyone can do it
if they love the Lord.

161
00:16:11,803 --> 00:16:14,473
Well, maybe so, Joe Bob. Maybe so.

162
00:16:14,848 --> 00:16:16,975
Here now, let me read you this:

163
00:16:18,393 --> 00:16:22,022
<i>When old age</i>
<i>shall this generation waste</i>

164
00:16:22,272 --> 00:16:25,192
<i>Thou shalt remain</i>
<i>in midst of other woe</i>

165
00:16:31,323 --> 00:16:35,494
<i>"Beauty is truth, truth beauty,"...</i>
<i>that is all</i>

166
00:16:35,744 --> 00:16:39,748
<i>Ye know on earth,</i>
<i>and all ye need to know.</i>

167
00:16:39,956 --> 00:16:41,875
Run, you little pissants, run!

168
00:16:42,125 --> 00:16:45,921
Tough it out!
You gotta be men like the rest of us.

169
00:16:46,129 --> 00:16:49,633
None of you pretty enough to be women.
Here, Joe Bob.

170
00:16:49,841 --> 00:16:52,761
Quit flapping your arms.
You look like a damn goose.

171
00:16:53,220 --> 00:16:55,847
Even a preacher's boy
ought to be in shape.

172
00:16:56,056 --> 00:16:58,141
What kind of female will you ever get?

173
00:16:59,184 --> 00:17:00,435
Tough it out!

174
00:17:02,729 --> 00:17:04,564
Run, you little pissants.

175
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:08,193
All right, off the court.

176
00:17:09,903 --> 00:17:13,740
If y'all didn't jack off so much,
maybe you could stay in shape.

177
00:17:13,949 --> 00:17:15,617
Come here a minute, Sonny.

178
00:17:18,995 --> 00:17:21,623
You do me a favour,
and I'll do you one.

179
00:17:21,873 --> 00:17:23,291
Sure, coach.

180
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:28,547
My old lady's got to go
to the doctor tomorrow.

181
00:17:28,755 --> 00:17:30,966
You know women.
Always something wrong.

182
00:17:31,174 --> 00:17:32,217
I guess.

183
00:17:33,844 --> 00:17:37,055
Take it from me. Anyway, I don't
have time to drive her.

184
00:17:37,264 --> 00:17:41,518
Now, if you'll do this for me,
I'll get you out of civics class.

185
00:17:41,935 --> 00:17:44,771
I'll be glad to.
The best offer I've had all day.

186
00:17:44,980 --> 00:17:49,276
Tell her you got to get back for
practice so she won't stay too long.

187
00:17:49,526 --> 00:17:51,736
I've got enough bills to pay already.

188
00:17:56,116 --> 00:18:01,121
" Know what the trouble is with you?
You ain't got no school spirit."

189
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:50,211
You need a haircut.

190
00:18:55,425 --> 00:18:58,303
Come on, Jimmie Sue.
We're hungry over here too.

191
00:18:58,511 --> 00:19:01,640
I'm coming. Hold your horses!

192
00:19:07,062 --> 00:19:09,689
Better watch it.
Here comes your mama.

193
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:22,118
We're having supper at home tonight.

194
00:19:22,369 --> 00:19:24,871
I expect you there
in 15 minutes, you hear?

195
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:28,291
Okay, Mama.
I was just giving the boys a ride.

196
00:19:52,607 --> 00:19:55,777
<i>Here's a tune that's been</i>
<i>on the hit list for some weeks.</i>

197
00:19:55,985 --> 00:19:57,070
<i>Tell us the name.</i>

198
00:20:00,031 --> 00:20:01,241
<i>What is it?</i>

199
00:20:02,117 --> 00:20:03,159
<i>What is it, huh?</i>

200
00:20:03,368 --> 00:20:05,745
<i>- "Shrimp Boats."</i>
<i>- You got it!</i>

201
00:20:08,623 --> 00:20:11,084
<i>Very good, Thomas.</i>
<i>You were in on that too.</i>

202
00:20:11,292 --> 00:20:13,586
<i>There's $120. We're going along fine.</i>

203
00:20:13,795 --> 00:20:16,214
<i>Now we come to City Limits.</i>
<i>This is...</i>

204
00:20:29,269 --> 00:20:30,770
Guess you hate me tonight.

205
00:20:30,979 --> 00:20:34,858
I love you, but I love Duane too.
Even if you don't like it.

206
00:20:35,066 --> 00:20:38,111
I don't care. I'd just hate
to see you marry him.

207
00:20:38,486 --> 00:20:40,280
You wouldn't be rich anymore.

208
00:20:40,488 --> 00:20:42,073
I don't care about money.

209
00:20:42,282 --> 00:20:43,825
You're pretty stupid then.

210
00:20:44,033 --> 00:20:47,620
You married Daddy when he was poor,
and he got rich, didn't he?

211
00:20:47,829 --> 00:20:50,457
Scared your daddy
into getting rich, beautiful.

212
00:20:50,665 --> 00:20:53,334
If Daddy could do it, Duane could too.

213
00:20:53,543 --> 00:20:56,045
Not married to you.
You're not scary enough.

214
00:20:56,254 --> 00:20:59,466
You're rich and miserable.
I don't want to be like you.

215
00:20:59,674 --> 00:21:01,301
Not much danger of that.

216
00:21:03,428 --> 00:21:04,846
- You slept with him?
- Mama!

217
00:21:05,054 --> 00:21:07,390
Go to the doctor
and arrange something...

218
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:11,644
...so you don't have to worry
about babies. You must be careful.

219
00:21:11,853 --> 00:21:15,690
But it's a sin unless you're married.
You know I wouldn't do that.

220
00:21:16,274 --> 00:21:17,901
Don't be so mealy-mouthed!

221
00:21:18,151 --> 00:21:19,819
I thought if you slept with him...

222
00:21:20,028 --> 00:21:22,947
...you might find there isn't
anything magic about him.

223
00:21:23,156 --> 00:21:25,283
Then we can send you
to a good school...

224
00:21:25,491 --> 00:21:26,784
I don't want to leave.

225
00:21:26,993 --> 00:21:29,954
Why can't I stay
and go to college in Wichita Falls?

226
00:21:30,163 --> 00:21:31,247
Because.

227
00:21:31,456 --> 00:21:34,417
Everything is flat and empty here.

228
00:21:34,667 --> 00:21:36,252
And nothing to do!

229
00:21:36,502 --> 00:21:37,879
Can I have some of that?

230
00:21:38,129 --> 00:21:40,298
Help yourself. Don't you have any?

231
00:21:40,506 --> 00:21:43,927
Yeah, but I feel like
smelling good right now.

232
00:21:45,345 --> 00:21:48,139
Don't you ever feel like
doing anything right now?

233
00:21:53,311 --> 00:21:55,271
